        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:18PM CDT by NWS Louisville KY</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Plum Springs, or 8 miles northeast of Bowling Green, moving southeast
at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowling Green, Scottsville, Plum Springs, Mount Victor, Smiths Grove,
Oakland, Three Forks, Hardcastle, Girkin, Greenhill, Austin, Settle,
Yesse, Loving, Tuckertown, Raley Ford, Sunnyside, Polkville,
Martinsville, and Motley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
